The paper deals with the enumeration of minimal dominating sets in graphs, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic aspect of the problem suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of line graphs and the modification of Berge's algorithm suggest that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of algorithmic graph theory (cs.AL).
